17. Qd1 b6 18. Bb2 Nh7 19. Bxd4 cxd4 20. Nd5 Bxd5 21. exd5 Ng5 22. Nxg5 hxg5
23. Bh3 Bf8 24. Qa4 {Matta,V (2274)-Ramakrishna,J (2253) New Delhi 2010 1/2-1/2
}) 10. dxe4 b6 {Black has an active position} 11. Nc4 {White threatens to win
material: Nc4xe5} Qc7 12. Re1 Be6 {Black threatens to win material: Be6xc4} 13.
Ne3 {Black has an active position} Rad8 14. b3 {Consolidates c4} Qc8 15. Ba3
Bh3 (15... Ng4 $5 $11) 16. Rad1 $14 Bxg2 17. Kxg2 {White king safety dropped}
Ng4 18. Nd5 Rde8 $2 (18... f5 $142 $5 {would keep Black alive} 19. h3 Nf6 20.
Nxf6+ Bxf6 $11) 19. b4 $16 Ne7 20. Qa4 (20. bxc5 $142 $5 bxc5 21. Qb3 $18)
20... Nxd5 $14 21. exd5 $4 {there were better ways to keep up the pressure} (
21. Rxd5 $142 {this is the best bet to save the position} f5 22. Nd2 $14 (22.
Qxa7 $4 {a poisoned pawn} fxe4 23. Rxe4 Nf6 $19)) 21... e4 $19 22. Ng5 (22. Ng1
Bxc3 23. d6 Qf5 $17 (23... Bxe1 24. d7 Qa8 25. dxe8=Q Rxe8 26. Rxe1 $16)) 22...
Qf5 23. Nh3 (23. Qc2 Qxg5 24. h3 $19) 23... Bxc3 24. Rf1 (24. Bc1 {there is
nothing better in the position} Bxe1 25. Rxe1 cxb4 26. Qxb4 $19) 24... e3 25.
bxc5 e2 26. cxb6 (26. Rh1 {does not solve anything} exd1=R 27. Qxd1 Re3 $19)
26... exf1=Q+ 27. Rxf1 Qxd5+ 28. Kg1 axb6 (28... Qh5 $142 {and the rest is a
matter of technique} 29. Kg2 Re2 $19) 29. Qxg4 (29. Bxf8 Nxf2 (29... Kxf8 $6
30. Qxg4 Qxa2 31. Qf3 $17) (29... Rxf8 $143 30. Qxg4 Qxa2 31. Qf3 $17) 30. Nxf2
Kxf8 31. Qa3+ Qc5 32. Qxc5+ bxc5 $19) 29... Qxa2 (29... f5 $142 {a pity that
Black didn't try this} 30. Qd1 Qxd1 31. Rxd1 Rf6 $19) 30. Bxf8 $17 Rxf8 31. Ng5
(31. Rd1 b5 $17) 31... Bg7 (31... b5 32. Rd1 $17) 32. Re1 (32. Qd7 Qa8 $17)
32... b5 33. Qd7 $2 (33. Rc1 h6 34. Nf3 Qa3 $19) 33... Qc4 (33... b4 $142 $19 {
keeps an even firmer grip}) 34. Re8 $4 {terrible, but the game is lost in any
case} (34. h4 $142 b4 35. Qa4 $19) 34... Qc1+ $19 35. Kg2 Qxg5 0-1

