Baku 1996 1-0}) 4... Bxc3+ $146 (4... Qxd5 5. Nf3 Nf6 6. Bd2 Bxc3 7. Bxc3 b6 8.
g3 Bb7 9. Bg2 Nbd7 10. O-O Qd6 11. Rc1 O-O 12. Qa4 a5 13. Bd2 c5 14. Bf4 Qe7
15. Rfd1 Nd5 16. Bg5 f6 17. Bd2 Ba6 18. e4 Nc7 19. Bf4 {Nei,I-Osnos,V
Leningrad 1963 1-0 (39)}) (4... exd5 $5 5. e3 Nf6 $11) 5. bxc3 $14 exd5 6. Nf3
Bg4 (6... Nc6 7. g3 $14) 7. h3 (7. Ne5 Bc8 $16) 7... Bxf3 8. exf3 Nf6 (8...
Qe7+ 9. Be3 Nf6 $16) 9. Bg5 (9. Ba3 $142 $5 $18) 9... O-O $14 {Black castles
and improves king safety} 10. Be2 Nbd7 11. O-O c6 {Controls b5} 12. c4 (12. Re1
Re8 $16) 12... dxc4 13. Bxc4 b5 {Black threatens to win material: b5xc4} 14.
Bb3 Qb6 15. Be3 Nd5 16. Qd2 (16. Bxd5 $5 cxd5 17. Qb3 $14) 16... a5 17. Bxd5
cxd5 18. Rac1 (18. Rfb1 Rab8 $11) 18... Rac8 19. Rc2 Rc4 {[%cal Rb6d4,Rc4d4,
Gd2d4,Ge3d4] Exerts pressure on the isolated pawn} 20. Rfc1 (20. a3 Qa6 $11)
20... Rfc8 $15 21. Qd3 Qg6 22. Qxg6 (22. Rxc4 dxc4 (22... Qxd3 $4 {Black goes
after material, which is his undoing} 23. Rxc8+ Nf8 24. Rb8 $18) (22... Rxc4 $6
23. Qa3 $11) (22... bxc4 $6 23. Qxg6 fxg6 24. Kf1 $15) 23. Qe4 h6 $15) 22...
hxg6 $17 23. Rxc4 Rxc4 {Black has new doubled pawns: g6+g7. Here comes the
goal-getter} (23... dxc4 24. d5 $17) 24. Kf1 Nb6 25. Ke2 Kf8 26. g4 (26. a3
Rxc1 27. Bxc1 Ke7 $11) 26... Ke7 27. h4 Na4 {Praise the knight!} 28. Kd2 b4 {
This push gains space} 29. Rxc4 $2 (29. Kd3 $142 $5 $15 {deserves consideration
}) 29... dxc4 $17 30. Kc2 $2 (30. d5 $142 $5 Nc3 31. Bd4 Nxa2 32. Bxg7 $19)
30... Kd6 31. f4 (31. Bf4+ Kd5 32. Bc7 Nc3 $19) 31... Nc3 32. a3 Kd5 33. axb4
axb4 34. g5 (34. Bd2 {no good, but what else?} Na2 35. Be1 Kxd4 36. Kb2 $19)
34... Ne2 35. f5 (35. Bd2 {a fruitless try to alter the course of the game}
Nxd4+ 36. Kb2 c3+ 37. Bxc3 bxc3+ 38. Kxc3 Ne2+ 39. Kb4 Nxf4 $19) 35... Nxd4+
36. Bxd4 (36. Kd2 c3+ 37. Kd3 $19) 36... Kxd4 37. f4 Ke4 38. h5 gxh5 39. f6 (
39. Kd2 {is not the saving move} Kxf4 40. f6 g6 41. Ke2 Ke4 42. Ke1 c3 43. Ke2
b3 44. Kf2 c2 45. Kg3 b2 46. Kf2 c1=Q 47. Kg3 Qh1 48. Kf2 b1=Q 49. Kg3 Qbe1#)
39... g6 (39... g6 40. Kd2 Kxf4 41. Ke2 Ke4 42. Ke1 c3 43. Ke2 b3 44. Kf1 Kf3
45. Kg1 b2 46. Kh1 Kg3 47. Kg1 b1=Q#) 0-1

