{C40: Latvian and Elephant Gambits} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Bc5 3. c3 $146 (3. Nxe5 d6
4. Nf3 Be6 5. d4 Bb6 6. Nc3 Nf6 7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O c5 9. d5 Bg4 10. Bf4 Re8 11.
h3 Bxf3 12. Qxf3 Nbd7 13. Bxd6 Rc8 14. Bb5 c4 15. Bxd7 Qxd7 16. e5 Bd4 17. Rfe1
Bxc3 {Mihalichenko,V (2407)-Tikhiy,S (2427) Azov 2010 1-0}) (3. Nxe5 $5 Nc6 4.
Nf3 $16) 3... d5 $14 4. d4 (4. exd5 Nf6 5. Nxe5 Qxd5 $14) 4... dxe4 5. dxc5 (5.
Nxe5 $5 {is an interesting idea} Bd6 6. Qb3 Bxe5 7. dxe5 $11) 5... Qxd1+ $15 6.
Kxd1 exf3 7. gxf3 {White has the pair of bishops} Nf6 8. Nd2 O-O {Black
castles and improves king safety} (8... Bf5 9. Rg1 $15) 9. Bd3 Rd8 10. Kc2 Nc6
11. Ne4 Nd5 12. Rg1 Kh8 13. Bg5 (13. Ng5 Rd7 14. Be4 Nf6 15. Bxc6 bxc6 $11)
13... f6 14. Bh4 Nf4 15. Rad1 (15. Bb5 Bf5 $15) 15... Be6 {Black threatens to
win material: Be6xa2} (15... Nxd3 16. Rxd3 Bf5 17. Bg3 $17) 16. Nxf6 $15 Nxd3
17. Rxd3 Rxd3 ({Worse is} 17... Bxa2 18. Rxd8+ Rxd8 19. Ne4 $16) 18. Kxd3 {
Opposite coloured bishops appeared} Bf5+ (18... Rf8 $142 $5 {and Black is
still in the game} 19. Ng4 Rxf3+ 20. Ne3 Bxa2 $15) 19. Ke3 Bg6 20. Nd7 (20. Nd5
Rc8 $16) 20... Re8 21. Bg3 $4 {[%cal Rd7e5,Rg3e5,Gc6e5,Ge8e5] Attacking the
isolated pawn on e5. a transit from better to worse} (21. b4 a6 $11) 21... Kg8
$4 {Black loses the upper hand} (21... Bf5 $142 22. Rd1 Rd8 $19) 22. f4 $4 {
allows the opponent back into the game} (22. b4 $142 $11 {the rescuing straw})
22... exf4+ $19 23. Kxf4 Re4+ (23... Re7 $5 {makes it even easier for Black}
24. Rd1 Be8 25. Nb6 cxb6 26. cxb6 axb6 27. Rd2 $19) 24. Kf3 Re7 25. Rd1 $4 {
sad, but how else could White save the game?} (25. Bxc7 $142 Rxd7 26. Bd6 $19)
25... Bh5+ 26. Kg2 Bxd1 0-1

